3 (2) The Cabinet for Health and Family Services shall:
4 (a) In consultation with the Board of Pharmacy, implement a pilot program to
5 study the effectiveness of in-home prescription drug disposal in Kentucky. The pilot
6 program shall:
7 1. Operate from January 1, 2026, to November 1, 2027;
8 2. Track the number of in-home drug disposal systems distributed by
9 participating pharmacies; and
10 3. Monitor local health data for a reduction in opioid-related overdoses and
11 deaths;
12 (b) Submit a report by December 1, 2027, to the Legislative Research
13 Commission for referral to the Interim Joint Committee on Health Services, which:
14 1. Lists the number of pharmacy locations participating in the pilot program;
15 2. Describes the activities undertaken by the cabinet to supply eligible patients
16 with:
17 a. In-home drug disposal systems; and
18 b. Medication safety information;
19 3. Surveys pharmacies to collect demographic information on:
20 a. Participating eligible patients;
21 b. Types of medication prescribed; and
22 c. The effective use of in-home drug disposal systems; and
23 4. Contains performance measures relating to the effectiveness of the program,
24 including but not limited to:
25 a. Changes in the participation rate of eligible patients; and
26 b. Engagement with pharmacists; and
27 (c) Develop a plan for cooperation between the cabinet and the Board of
